---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lang = 'en';
---
<Layout title="PDPL / GDPR | Harezm Technology" lang={lang}>
    <div class="pt-32 pb-24 bg-surface min-h-screen">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8 md:px-0">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-headline font-bold text-on-background mb-8">Personal Data Protection Policy (PDPL / GDPR)</h1>
            <div class="space-y-6 text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed font-light">
                <p>As Harezm Technology and Consulting ("Harezm" or "Company"), the security and privacy of your personal data is one of our highest priorities. As a "Data Controller" under the Personal Data Protection Law No. 6698 ("PDPL") in Turkey and relevant international data protection laws (e.g., GDPR), we process and protect your personal data in compliance with the Law.</p>
                
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-background mt-10 mb-4">1. Purpose of Processing Personal Data</h2>
                <p>The personal data we collect is processed for the purposes of completely providing our software architecture, SAP consulting, and other e-transformation services, fulfilling operational requirements, performing our legal responsibilities, and maintaining corporate communication.</p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-background mt-10 mb-4">2. Method and Legal Basis for Data Collection</h2>
                <p>Your personal data is collected via communication forms filled out through our website, emails sent to us, LinkedIn, and other digital communication channels. This data is processed based on the legal grounds of the performance of a contract, legal obligations of the data controller, and legitimate interests framework.</p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-background mt-10 mb-4">3. Data Transfer and Recipients</h2>
                <p>As a rule, Harezm does not share your personal data with third parties. However, in order to resolve legal disputes and fulfill legal obligations arising from the legislation, it may be shared with judicial authorities and legally authorized public/private institutions with the necessary security measures in place.</p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-background mt-10 mb-4">4. Your Rights as a Data Subject</h2>
                <p>You can convey your requests regarding your personal data by contacting our Company at <strong>info@harezm.com.tr</strong>. Your requests will be reviewed and responded to free of charge as soon as possible, and no later than thirty days.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
